# Blocking Feature API Test
# Administrator User Blocking/Unblocking Feature

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5177
@adminToken = your_admin_jwt_token_here
@userId = 1

### 1. Get All Accounts (shows Blocked field)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/administrator/account
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Block User
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/administrator/account/{{userId}}/block
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Unblock User  
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/administrator/account/{{userId}}/unblock
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Get All Accounts Again (verify blocked status changed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/administrator/account
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

###
# Note: Replace {{adminToken}} with an actual JWT token from admin authentication
# Note: Replace {{userId}} with an actual user ID from the database
# 
# Expected behavior:
# - Only users with Administrator role can access these endpoints
# - Block endpoint sets user.Blocked = true
# - Unblock endpoint sets user.Blocked = false  
# - All endpoints return appropriate error messages for validation failures